&lt;p&gt;This is a contract role built for someone who brings real curiosity, a bias toward execution, and a genuine desire to work on something that matters: Pelago is devoted to making substance use support accessible to everyone. You&#39;ll get meaningful ownership from day one — and a front-row seat to how a fast-scaling digital health company drives utilization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU&#39;LL DO&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;- Build client-facing collateral&lt;/strong&gt; — pitch decks, talk tracks, and supporting materials that help employer clients decide to promote Pelago to their workforce&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;-&amp;nbsp; Partner with Customer Success &amp;amp; Implementation&lt;/strong&gt; — support customer success team (CSMs) and implementation managers in client-facing meetings with marketing updates, act as a marketing resource for managing launching and legacy accounts, and work with both teams toward client-specific enrollment goals and customer satisfaction&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;-&amp;nbsp; Support member enrollment campaigns&lt;/strong&gt; — review marketing communications for quality and accuracy, manage client approval queues, and filter client feedback back to creative teams producing campaigns&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;-&amp;nbsp; Track campaign performance&lt;/strong&gt; — pull enrollment data, measure campaign impact, and share clear summaries of what is and isn&#39;t working with clients to inform strategic decision-making.&lt;/p&gt;
